                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">612.119/2839</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of a Conversation between the Secretary of State
                        and the Mexican Chargé</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Diego-Fernandez</hi>), <hi
                        rend="italic">April 22, 1920</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1920-04-22">April 22, 1920</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>The Chargé d’Affaires of Mexico called to discuss the friction and disorders
                    along the border, emphasizing the desire that the Carranza Government be
                    permitted to import arms and ammunition and renewed his warnings against the
                    irregular shipment of arms and ammunition which are supposed to be reaching the
                    rebellious elements in Northern Mexico.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
